                <h1>Immigration in the U.S.: A Brief History</h1>
                <p>Throughout its history, the U.S. has been shaped by waves of immigration, beginning with European settlers in the 1600s. The 19th century saw a surge of Irish and German immigrants, often fleeing famine and persecution. The 20th century brought diverse groups, including Italians, Jews, and Asians, each contributing to America's rich cultural tapestry.</p>
